The Storage summary File System section might show inaccurate results.

After further investigation, the Java class that gets the storage size calculates the total size and the free space to get the used space value.

This might not be accurate since the classss gets the total freespace and not the actual usable space by the user/process.

This causes incosistencies in the information from the 'df -h' command.

Long story short, we need to find some more accurate way to present the data.

The method for the space calcualtion:

public FileStoreStorageSummary(List<File> binariesFolders, BinaryProvidersInfo<Map<String, String>> binaryProvidersInfo) {
 this.binariesFolders = binariesFolders;
 binariesStorageTemplate = binaryProvidersInfo.template;
 if (binariesFolders != null && !binariesFolders.isEmpty()) {
 freeSpace = binariesFolders.stream().mapToLong(File::getFreeSpace).sum();
 totalSpace = binariesFolders.stream().mapToLong(File::getTotalSpace).sum();
 usedSpace = totalSpace - freeSpace;
 } else {
 freeSpace = 0;
 totalSpace = 0;
 usedSpace = 0;
 }

 if (isFullDb(binaryProvidersInfo) || isCacheFs(binaryProvidersInfo)) {
 cacheSize = getFirstCacheMaxSize(binaryProvidersInfo);
 } else {
 cacheSize = -1L;
 }
}

