02/Jul/19 1:59 AM;Vedaraman;[~alexeiv]: I am a fellow jfrog user myself. I had a similar issue and this is the information I have found out so far

With the installation of JFrog Artifactory, we also get artifactory.war in a path */artifactory/webapps/artifactory.war* similar to that

This is the war file that gets deployed onto Tomcat and serves as UI for us.

The war file has many packages jar files in them. One of them is *artifactory-core-6.5.9.jar*

The core jar file has the following class file in it

org/artifactory/repo/service/RepositoryServiceImpl.class

I decompiled the class file and noticed the following

public BasicStatusHolder undeploy(RepoPath repoPath, boolean calcMavenMetadata, boolean pruneEmptyFolders) {
      String repoKey = repoPath.getRepoKey();
      StoringRepo storingRepo = this.storingRepositoryByKey(repoKey);
      BasicStatusHolder statusHolder = new BasicStatusHolder();
      if (storingRepo == null) {
         statusHolder.error("Could find storing repository by key '" + repoKey + "'", log);
         return statusHolder;
      } else {
         PathDeletionContext pathDeletionContext = (new org.artifactory.repo.local.PathDeletionContext.Builder(storingRepo, repoPath.getPath(), statusHolder)).assertOverwrite(false).build();
         this.assertDelete(pathDeletionContext);
         if (!statusHolder.isError()) {
            try {
               storingRepo.undeploy((new DeleteContext(repoPath)).calculateMavenMetadata(calcMavenMetadata));
            } catch (CancelException var9) {
              {color:#d04437} *statusHolder.error("Undeploy was canceled by user plugin", var9.getErrorCode(), var9, log);*{color}
            }
         }

         if (pruneEmptyFolders && !repoPath.isRoot()) {
            this.pruneService.prune(repoPath.getParent());
         }

         return statusHolder;
      }
   }

 

As you can see, Undeploy was cancelled by user plugin is hardcoded in the error handling - which comes by default with the installtion of Artifactory.

Jfrog will need to update this in one of the releases, such that our custom message will be used instead of the default one

