The documentation for Artifact Version Search (http://www.jfrog.com/confluence/display/RTF/Artifactory+REST+API#ArtifactoryRESTAPI-ArtifactVersionSearch) notes:
{quote}
Search can be limited to specific repositories (local, remote and virtual) by settings the repos parameter.
{quote}

The documentation for Checksum SEARCH (http://www.jfrog.com/confluence/display/RTF/Artifactory+REST+API#ArtifactoryRESTAPI-ChecksumSearch) notes:
{quote}
Can limit search to specific repositories (local or caches).
{quote}

The important difference to note is that Artifact Virtual Search supports virtual repo, but Checksum Search does not.  I tested this empirically with Artifactory 3.0.2, and the documentation is correct.

As with RTFACT-6661, this seems like a very odd difference between two search operations.  I don't know which is "right", but it seems to me like it ought to be consistent.  At least in this case (unlike in that case), the difference is documented.

